title: kegg-graph
text: map differential expression results nodes KEGG pathway graph can use map_results_to_nodes(). input function graph object built kegg_to_graph() list differential expression results tables single differential expression results table. can also pass input map_results_to_nodes() single data.frame differential expression results. dataframe must contain least two columns: one KEGG feature IDs (without organism prefix) another values map nodes (e.g., log2 fold changes). can pass function names columns differ default ones parameters feature_column value_column. Note KEGG IDs without organism prefix ENTREZ IDs genes. feature types (e.g., compounds) need make sure IDs differential expression results table match KEGG IDs used graph. defualt parameters : feature_column: “KEGG_ids” value_column: “log2FoldChange” multiple differential expression results tables (example one metabolomics one transcriptomics) map nodes can pass list lists. sublist must contain following elements: de_table: data.frame differential expression results. value_column: name column de_table containing values map nodes. feature_column: name column de_table containing feature IDs (e.g., ENTREZ IDs) correspond KEGG ids graph (without organism prefix).

text: use Kegg pathway visualization function need kegg id pathway want visualize. can run function kegg_to_graph get igraph representation pathway. wish plot directly visnetwork enough add parameter return_type = "visnetwork". can use function map_results_to_nodes map differential expression results nodes graph. can provide either single data frame list data frames containing differential expression results. data frame column feature IDs (e.g., ENTREZID) column values want map (e.g., logFC log2FoldChange). using single data frame can like :
